This paper deals with communication networks and their optimization in terms of throughput and age of information constraints. The paper focuses on the fifth generation (5G) technology, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with communication networks and their optimization, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the allocation of resources and policies for power allocation, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of randomized policies, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of fading channels, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
